    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7, then rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat, once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot, then rinse your <strong>blanched edamame beans</strong> under<strong> cold running water</strong>, add to the pot with the rice and keep covered until serving \u2013 this is your <strong>edamame brown rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sesame-chicken-katsu-with-edamame-brown-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, take your <strong>chicken </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Boil a kettle, then add your <strong>chicken</strong> to a <strong>tin foil-</strong>lined baking tray</p><p>Sprinkle over your <strong>black sesame seeds</strong> and season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, then put the tray in the oven for 18-20 min or until cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>sesame chicken</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sesame-chicken-katsu-with-edamame-brown-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel half your <strong>carrot[s]</strong>, until you end up with a pile of carrot ribbons</p><p>Grate the <strong>remaining carrot[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sesame-chicken-katsu-with-edamame-brown-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large pot with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>grated</strong> <strong>carrot</strong>, your<strong> ginger paste</strong> and the <strong>chopped shallot </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 3 min or until slightly softened</p><p>Once slightly softened, add your <strong>curry powder</strong> and <strong>umami seasoning</strong> and cook for 2 min further until fragrant, then once fragrant, add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong>,<strong> </strong>stir it all together and cook for 1 min</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sesame-chicken-katsu-with-edamame-brown-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> to the pot and reduce the heat to low</p><p>Add your <strong>soy sauce</strong> and <strong>tomato ketchup</strong> and stir it all together</p><p>Cook for 5-7 min or until the sauce has thickened to a curry-like consistency, then blitz until smooth with a <strong>(stick) blender </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>katsu sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sesame-chicken-katsu-with-edamame-brown-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>rice vinegar </strong>with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>dressing</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>carrot ribbons</strong> to the bowl and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>dressed carrot ribbons</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sesame-chicken-katsu-with-edamame-brown-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once done, transfer the chicken to a clean board and slice finely</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sesame-chicken-katsu-with-edamame-brown-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>sliced sesame chicken</strong> over the <strong>katsu sauce</strong>, with the <strong>edamame brown rice</strong> and <strong>dressed carrot ribbons</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
